newsitem.title: USA: U.S. crude, products firm in ACCESS after hours.
newsitem.headline: U.S. crude, products firm in ACCESS after hours.

text.p: U.S. crude oil and products prices firmed in thin after-hours ACCESS trade on Monday, reversing modest declines in the floor session.
NYMEX October crude traded $23.80 a barrel, up seven cents on 225 lots traded early in the session after failing to break $24.00 a barrel resistance earlier in the day.
October heating oil firmed to 66.05 cents a gallon on 69 lots traded, a 0.10 cent gain from the earlier close at 65.95 cents.
Front-month unleaded gasoline was indicated higher, bid 64.20 cents a gallon, asked 64.50 cents on 13 lots traded after closing at 64.09 cents a gallon in the floor session.
